Description: GMRS/Amateur/Part 90 repeater controller daemon
 kerchunkd is a lightweight C11 repeater controller for Retevis RT97L and
 similar GMRS, Amateur (Part 97), and Business/Industrial (Part 90) repeaters.
 Interfaces via a RIM-Lite v2 USB radio interface (CM108AH chipset) using
 hidraw for COR/PTT and PortAudio for audio I/O. All CTCSS/DCS/DTMF decoding
 and CW ID generation is handled in software using libplcode.
 .
 24 dynamically loaded modules: repeater state machine, CW ID (FCC 95.1751),
 caller identification, DTMF commands, voicemail, weather, time, NWS alerts,
 TTS (ElevenLabs), parrot/echo, CDR, statistics, recording, TX encoding,
 emergency mode, OTP authentication, courtesy tones, GPIO, logging, web
 dashboard, webhook notifications, voice scrambler, SDR channel monitor,
 and FreeSWITCH autopatch.
 .
 Embedded HTTPS web dashboard with real-time SSE event stream, WebSocket
 audio monitoring, and WebSocket push-to-talk. Native JSON API with NDJSON
 event streaming. Interactive CLI with tab completion.
 .
 This package provides the kerchunkd daemon, the kerchunk CLI, the
 kerchunk-diag diagnostic tool, all modules, sound files, web dashboard,
 and systemd service.
